<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="loose-adj">loose <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /luːs/    美 /luːs/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-tight">1.★ <strong>松的；宽松的【tight】；松散的</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don't wear loose clothes in the lab.
不要在实验室里穿宽松的衣服。</p><footer>2017 全国改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If the structure of your speech is loose and confused, chances are that your thinking is also disordered and confused.
如果你的演讲结构松散混乱，很可能你的思维也同样混乱不清。</p><footer>2011 北京</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>自由的；不严谨的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This dog must not be left loose.
这条狗一定要拴住。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a loose term
不严谨的术语</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="let-loose">let loose</h3>
<p>1.<strong>释放；放任：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Just close your eyes and let loose your imagination.
闭上眼睛，尽情发挥你的想象力。</p></div>

<h3 id="loose-lips-sink-ships">Loose lips sink ships.</h3>
<p>1.<strong>祸从口出。/ 言多必失。</strong>  </p></div>